subSection.paragraph:
Pea (
Pisum sativum
) branching mutant plants used in this study were derived from various cultivars of pea after ethyl methanesulfonate (EMS) mutagenesis and were described previously ( Rameau et al., 1997 ). The rms1-10 ( M 3T-884) and rms3-5 ( M 2T-32) mutants were obtained from the dwarf cv Térèse. Plants were grown in a greenhouse under long days as described in ( Braun et al., 2012 ).

